fulltitle: War and political repression: who is responsible? G. William Domhoff (1969)
title: War and political repression: who is responsible? G. William Domhoff (1969)
_filename: _War and political repression - who is responsible G. William Domhoff (1969).mp4
description:
War and political repression was the topic of the commission of inquiry held in the Pauley Ballroom on January 16, 17 and 18 sponsored by the Stop the Draft Week Committee on the occasion of the beginning of the Oakland Seven's conspiracy trial. The speaker on this program is G. William Domhoff of the U.C. faculty at Santa Cruz and the author of the book, Who Rules America. He talks about the foreign policy establishment. 

Broadcast in January, 1969.
